reviewText: A collection of brief sets by well-known and not so well-know comedians. Engaging.

Some of these comedians were very funny and you certainly get a lot of variety.  Definitely worth the cheap price.  I loved Grant Turner's innocent bystander routine and I believe Greg Travis is "David Sleaze-Punk Magician" from the 80's. A must watch of that skit on YouTube.

When I saw this, I thought, "Neat, more of the "southern comics" I like so much."  Wrong.....If I had been able to read the back of the DVD before purchasing, I would not have bought this. These segments are old....really old.  As in 20+ years old.  I am not happy with this item, the age of the clips should have been posted in the item discription.
